article.headline: Northern Arizona 94, Sacramento State 71
article.story: SACRAMENTO, Calif. (AP) -- Stephen Sir made seven three-pointers to finish with 25 points off the bench as Northern Arizona beat Sacramento State 94-71 Saturday night. Ryan McCurdy had 18 points, 13 rebounds, and two blocked shots, and Tyrone Bazy added 15 points for the Lumberjacks (9-8, 4-2 Big Sky). The Lumberjacks hit six 3-point shots in the first half to take a 42-32 halftime lead. Sir, who had 14 points in the first half, accounted for four of NAU's treys. The Hornets cut NAU's lead to four on a basket by Davon Roberts at the 14:34 mark to make the score 54-50. But the Lumberjacks regrouped to go on a 34-12 run, finished by a Sir basket that put the score at 88-62 with 2:37 left. NAU made 17 of 22 shots in the second half (77.3 percent). Haron Hargraves added 19 points and Angel Alamos 18 led the Hornets (7-11, 2-4 Big Sky).
